Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop onto a large
#baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to
coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%grams}. Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a medium #bowl{}, combine the lime juice, a drizzle of @oil{} and a pinch of
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the @coleslaw mix{120%grams} and toss to coat in the
dressing, then set aside.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Add the @British beef mince{240%grams} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a
#spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Once the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat, then stir in the
garlic and @tomato puree{30%grams}. Cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir in the @chipotle paste{20%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things milder),
@chicken stock paste{10%grams}, @honey{1%tbsp} and @water{100%ml}. Stir to combine,
bring to the boil and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pop the @plain taco tortillas{4} (2 per person) into the oven to warm
through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once the sauce has thickened, remove from the heat. Taste and season with @salt{}
and @pepper{} if needed.

Lay the tortillas onto your #plates{} and top with the chipotle beef and coleslaw.

Sprinkle over the cheese and a pinch of lime zest to finish.

Serve with the wedges alongside.

> TIP: Tacos are best enjoyed eaten by hand - get stuck in!

Enjoy!